cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with transmission of information and optimization of transmission time. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses optimal offline and online policies for transmitter and receiver, which can be viewed as a game between the two entities. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with energy harvesting systems and control of transmission power and ON-OFF profile. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with transmission of bits, which can be considered as multimedia data. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with transmission of information between a transmitter and receiver.
